[{"category":"section","location":"#MicroGPT","page":"Home","text":"Documentation for MicroGPT.\n\n","title":"MicroGPT"},{"category":"type","location":"#MicroGPT.Tokenizer","page":"Home","text":"Tokenizer\n\nA character-level tokenizer built from a corpus of documents.\n\nFields:\n\nuchars: sorted, deduplicated vocabulary characters.\nchar2id: reverse lookup from character to its token ID.\nbos: boundary token ID used to wrap every encoded sequence.\nvocab_size: number of distinct tokens, including the bos token.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.Tokenizer"},{"category":"method","location":"#MicroGPT.Tokenizer-Tuple{Vector{String}}","page":"Home","text":"Tokenizer(docs::Vector{String})\n\nBuild a Tokenizer from docs. The vocabulary is the sorted set of all characters appearing in the corpus.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.Tokenizer"},{"category":"method","location":"#MicroGPT.backward!-Tuple{Value}","page":"Home","text":"backward!(v::Value)\n\nCompute the gradients of v with respect to every Value in its computation graph via backpropagation.\n\nThis mutates the v.grad and of all Values in its graph. Gradients are accumulated, so reset them between independent backward passes if a node is reused.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.backward!"},{"category":"method","location":"#MicroGPT.decode-Tuple{Tokenizer, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"Home","text":"decode(tok::Tokenizer, ids::AbstractVector{<:Integer}) -> String\n\nDecode token IDs back into a string, stripping boundary tokens. Throws ArgumentError if ids contains an ID outside the vocabulary.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.decode"},{"category":"method","location":"#MicroGPT.encode-Tuple{Tokenizer, AbstractString}","page":"Home","text":"encode(tok::Tokenizer, doc::AbstractString) -> Vector{Int}\n\nEncode doc into token IDs, wrapped with the boundary token at both ends. Throws ArgumentError if doc contains a character outside the vocabulary.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.encode"}]
